    <section>
        <h2 id="turn">Turn</h2>

        <h3 id="wind-up">Wind Up</h3>
        <p>
            When legs, hips, and shoulders are moved simultaneously to create a rotational momentum. Usually used from a static starting position.
        </p>

        <h3 id="commence-to-turn">Commence to Turn<br />(aka. Lateral Leg Movement Principle)</h3>
        <p>
            Used in <strong>left turns</strong> to prevent the lady from crossing the middle line of the man during turns.<br />
            Used in <strong>right turns</strong> when there is a rotation before the previous step and the first step of the current figure.
        </p>
