    <section>
        <h2 id="type-of-sway">Type of Sway</h2>
        <p>
            A sway is a stretch of one side of the body; towards or away from the moving leg. Used for balance, speed or initiation of movement, or aesthetics.<br />
            Moving in the opposite direction of the movement decreases speed and improves stability.<br />
            Moving in the direction of the movement increases speed and decreases stability.
        </p>
        <dl>
            <dt id="technical-sway">Technical Sway</dt>
            <dd>Entire body from foot to thead is stretched. Action can be perceived in the hip.</dd>
            <dt id="releasing-sway">Releasing Sway / Broken Sway</dt>
            <dd>Only the upper part of the body is involved. Position of the hip is not affected. One side is shortened and the other is stretched.</dd>
            <dt id="cosmetic-sway">Cosmetic Sway</dt>
            <dd>Shoulders and shoulder blades are stretched slightly without moving the head. The other side of the body is relaxed.</dd>
        </dl>
        <h2 id="extension">Extension</h2>
        <p>
            Stretch of the front of the upper body in relation to the back of the upper body.<br />
            The stretch starts at the head, neck, and chest and follows in the lower part abdomen (belly), and lumbar area (lower back).
        </p>
    </section>

